geant4 tutorial 2007 slac geant4 tutorial 2007 slac redwood room 14 18 may 2007 this is a four day hands on tutorial course based on geant4 version 8.2 p01 lectures cover all aspects of geant4 from basic installation through advanced topics and will be interspersed with examples that build a progressively more complex application extensible to real use the course should be of interest both to complete novices and to those who already have some basic familiarity with geant4 participants are expected to have a reasonable knowledge of c++ agenda the tutorial starts at 14 00 on monday may 14th and adjourns at 17 00 on friday may 18th there is no tutorial on the morning of wednesday may 16th due to the unavailability of the meeting room but a slac site tour may be arranged by request the final agenda includes links to all of the presentations laptop required users should bring a geant4 capable laptop with a wireless internet connection slac will not offer any computers for tutorial participants minimum required free disk space to install geant4 is about 500mb 1 gb for windows visualc++ supported systems and c++ compilers are listed here though we will briefly cover the installation of geant4 and related libraries on the first day of the tutorial we strongly encourage recommend the participants to install geant4 in advance of the tutorial full instructions of installing geant4 8.2 p01 are here if you have questions about whether your laptop is appropriate or problems about installing geant4 see the geant4 installation guide the geant4 installation and configuration discussion forum or contact the tutorial organizers registration the course will be given at no charge but pre registration is requested since capacity will be strictly limited to 50 attendees registration has already hit to the maximum capacity and we closed the registration thank you for your interest on our tutorial tutorial materials are publicly available from the agenda page accomodation travel and visa information is available here organizing committee makoto asai joseph perl dennis wright slac geant4 team contact the tutorial organizers
